=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Protect methyl 2-amino-4-tert-butylthiophene-5-carboxylate with Boc2O/base to give tert-butyl (5-(methoxycarbonyl)-4-tert-butylthiophen-2-yl)carbamate | Step 2: Reduce the ester with LiAlH4 to tert-butyl (4-tert-butyl-5-(hydroxymethyl)thiophen-2-yl)carbamate | Step 3: Convert CH2OH to CH2Br with PBr3 to give tert-butyl (4-tert-butyl-5-(bromomethyl)thiophen-2-yl)carbamate | Step 4: Displace bromide with NH3 (or via N3 then reduction) to form tert-butyl (5-(aminomethyl)-4-tert-butylthiophen-2-yl)carbamate | Step 5: Couple this side-chain amine with Boc-glycine (BocNHCH2CO2H, EDC/HATU) to obtain tert-butyl (5-((2-((tert-butoxycarbonyl)amino)acetylamino)methyl)-4-tert-butylthiophen-2-yl)carbamate | Step 6: Remove both Boc groups with TFA or HCl/dioxane to give 2-amino-N-((2-amino-4-tert-butylthiophen-5-yl)methyl)acetamide | Step 7: In the convergent final step, prepare p-tolyl isocyanate from p-toluidine (e.g. triphosgene/base) and react it with the thiophene 2-amine from Step 6 to install the unsymmetrical urea, furnishing Cc1ccc(NC(=O)Nc2cc(C(C)(C)C)sc2CNC(=O)CN)cc1.

